article.headline: St. Thomas earns 66-50 win against Chicago State
article.description: — Brooks Allen and Ben Nau scored 17 points as St. Thomas beat Chicago State 66-50 on Sunday.
article.linkText: St. Thomas earns 66-50 win against Chicago State
article.story: CHICAGO -- — Brooks Allen and Ben Nau scored 17 points as St. Thomas beat Chicago State 66-50 on Sunday. Allen shot 6 for 10, including 4 for 6 from beyond the arc for the Tommies (6-4). Nau was 6 for 8, including 5 for 7 from beyond the arc. Noble Crawford led the way for the Cougars (3-9) with 12 points, six rebounds and four steals. Chicago State also got 12 points and two steals from Wesley Cardet Jr.. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
